name: United Kingdom
story: The birthplace of afternoon tea culture, the UK has embraced specialty coffee with remarkable enthusiasm. From traditional tea rooms evolving into modern coffee houses to innovative roasters pushing boundaries, British coffee culture blends heritage with contemporary excellence.

name: Turkey
story: Turkey's coffee heritage dates back to the Ottoman Empire, making it one of the world's oldest coffee cultures. Turkish coffee is UNESCO-recognized, and modern specialty coffee shops now complement traditional coffeehouses, creating a unique blend of ancient traditions and contemporary brewing methods.

name: Germany
